  <relatedmaterial id="aspace_3d4185b072909cc381a46c55f5a6fb0d">
    <head>Related Materials</head>
<p>The Center for Brooklyn History holds the following related collections: </p><p>- Emanuel Celler Collection, 1912-1981 (BCMS.0017)</p><p>- Major Owens Collection, 1957-2013 (BCMS.0078)</p><p>- Joseph R. Lentol Papers, 1951-2020 (CBHM.0004)</p><p>- The Brooklyn Daily Eagle photographs (BCMS.0002) has photographs of Joseph L. Pfeifer</p><p>The Congressional Record from Dr. Pfeifer's time in office is held by the Library of Congress and online at Congress.gov. Bills and resolutions are held at the Law Library of Congress. </p>  </relatedmaterial>
  <separatedmaterial id="aspace_203f54a68096bdea98e31a2f4022d935">
    <head>Separated Materials</head>
<p>Newspaper clippings regarding organized crime in the 1970s and 1980s and an unannotated map of Europe were determined to be out of scope and returned to the donor.</p>  </separatedmaterial>
