  <dsc><c id="aspace_c5d178ec8932b70e271e6f7980fea128" level="series"><did><unittitle>Series 1: Pfeifer and McKean family papers</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/3/archival_objects/457034</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1890/2013" type="inclusive">circa 1900-2013</unitdate></did><arrangement id="aspace_fe2e975a8e450f41a9906b58079894ea"><head>Arrangement</head><p>This series is arranged chronologically.</p></arrangement><scopecontent id="aspace_ab230dc622e5b2ee7b698d560f37c817"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Series 1: Pfeifer and McKean family papers, circa 1900-2013, includes materials related to the families of Joseph L. Pfeifer and Adeline McKean, their married life, and the family they raised in Brooklyn. Types of materials include photographs, news clippings, programs, and certificates. </p><p>Some ephemera and news clippings reference activities of their children and Dr. Pfeifer's brother. Their son Joseph Lawrence Pfeifer, Jr. graduated from Xavier High School in 1940. His brother Thomas attended West Point, graduating in 1946. Dr. Pfeifer's brother, Rev. Herman J. Pfeifer was pastor of St. Alphonsus Church in Greenpoint.</p><p>Also included is a photograph of the couple and news clippings from when they celebrated their golden anniversary in 1967. At the end of the series are published obituaries of Dr. Pfeifer and a biography written in 2013 by his grandson Peter Peff. </p></scopecontent><c id="aspace_a92e31936f71cff912c1ea1fd9f45019" level="file"><did><unittitle>McKean Family photographs</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/3/archival_objects/457038</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1890/1910" type="inclusive"> circa 1900</unitdate><container id="aspace_6a9a7c3305681d0204a9b52d6255e7ea" label="Mixed Materials" type="Box">1</container><container id="aspace_928a97344dbda92589608e809b947c49" parent="aspace_6a9a7c3305681d0204a9b52d6255e7ea" type="Folder">1</container></did></c><c id="aspace_01d838dc7f