1c9f04a5751cb0d0b8" level="series"><did><unittitle>Series 3: U.S. House of Representatives files</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/3/archival_objects/457036</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1919/1950" type="inclusive">1919-1950</unitdate><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1934/1950" type="bulk">1934-1950</unitdate></did><arrangement id="aspace_8d45c26ce697188cdb66038c98224b11"><head>Arrangement</head><p>This series is arranged chronologically.</p></arrangement><scopecontent id="aspace_32390e4adf9d1cdabfdf7dbbc168e2b1"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Series 3: U.S. House of Representatives files, 1919-1950, includes materials related to Dr. Joseph Pfeifer's time as a United States congressman representing Greenpoint, Williamsburg, and Bushwick, as well as his election and re-election campaigns.</p><p>Materials related to Dr. Pfeifer's election campaigns in 1934, 1936, and 1938 are well-represented in this series. Materials include letters of endorsement from democratic clubs and local medical organizations; flyers, feathers, ribbons, and a banner advertising Dr. Pfeifer's campaign; and newspaper clippings collected to use in a 1936 attack ad against Democratic club leader Jerome G. Ambro. Seating charts and a photograph from the testimonial dinner held for Dr. Pfeifer at Hotel St. George after his first election victory are also in this series. Re-election campaigns post-1938 are not represented.</p><p>Dr. Pfeifer's time on the Committee of Foreign Affairs pre- and post-World War II is also well-represented in this series. Photographs, correspondence, and itineraries show his trips to Europe, Egypt, and Morocco, especially his time at Camp Bari, a displaced persons camp in Italy, and in Vatican City for his audience with Pope Pius XII. </p><p>Representatives Luther A. Johnson, Pete Jarman, Emily Taft Douglas, Robert B. Chiperfield, Bartel J. Jonkman, and Charles L. Gerlach were present on the 1945 tour of Western Europe and are depicted in the related photographs. Jacob Javits and Thomas Pfeifer are depicted in the photographs from the 1949 Committee on Foreign Affairs tour.</p><p>Dr. Pfeifer kept an autograph book during the 1945 tour of Western Europe, which includes signatures of people he met on the trip, such as Alexander Fleming, Prince Faisal of Saudi Arabia, Abd al-Ilah of Iraq, Vassily Solokovsky, Georgy Zukhov, members of the UK House of Commons, members of the Belgian, Dutch, and Greek parliaments, and employees of the Casino de Monte-Carlo.</p><p>Photographs of Newtown Creek in Greenpoint and copies of river and harbor bills show Dr. Pfeifer's work on environmental protection for local waters.</p></scopecontent><c id="aspace_3a621c54249ba8756ee09fafb80bfc1f" level="file"><did><unittitle>River and harbor bills</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/3/archival_objects/468942</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1919/1942" type="inclusive">1919-1942</unitdate><container id="aspace_f4e701d28dd2e655fc29216bfd8d7d9d" label="Mixed Materials" type="Box">1</container><container id="aspace_331913aa2b6518ac00d0010a963fd151" parent="aspace_f4e701d28dd2e655fc29216bfd8d7d9d" type="Folder">26</container></did></c><c id="aspace_1785af8088a3c73c0120a2d2691b9efb" level="file"><did><unittitle>Photographs of Newtown Creek</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/3/archival_objects/468943</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1924/1944" type="inclusive">circa 1934</unitdate><container id="aspace_71654f7d7f9a0cff4951cdd257a998a0" label="Mixed Materials" type="Box">1</container><container id="aspace_33f61c58e5905a149d6b456cc51cdf39" parent="aspace_71654f7d7f9a0cff4951cdd257a998a0" type="Folder">27</container></did></c><c id="aspace_4e52497c8eaa147ab8cc0371ab91a6b6" level="file"><did><unittitle>Election campaign promotional materials</unittitle><unitid type="aspace_uri">/repositories/3/archival_objects/457050</unitid><unitdate datechar="creation" normal="1934/1934">1